userstories.title: My Father Patrick McCarthy's Garden
userstories.author: Maria McCarthy
userstories.story:
the dog who ran
down the street real real good
was never bothered by anyones conscience
that didnt ever need bothering
because he didnt like it when sticky suckers touched
the tips of his paws so gingerly in the summer winds
and animals who lick the tips of dandelions know how sweet the sound
of sweet sweet summer violets can be.
